---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Report a Contractual Breach
description: "Report a contractual breach to Manchester LMC. All reports treated in strict confidence."
mainClass: page-breach-report
showContactStrip: false
showDisclaimer: true
permalink: /support/breach-report/
---

  <section class="page-hero" aria-label="Page header">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-hero-content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <span class="breadcrumb-sep" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
          <a href="/support/">Support</a>
          <span class="breadcrumb-sep" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
          <span aria-current="page">Report a Contractual Breach</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Report a Contractual Breach</h1>
        <p>Submit a confidential breach report to Manchester LMC for investigation</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:780px;margin:0 auto">
        <div class="alert alert--info" role="note">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-3);align-items:flex-start">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:2px"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
            <p style="margin:0;line-height:1.6"><strong>All breach reports are treated in strict confidence.</strong> Submission does not constitute a formal complaint but enables the LMC to identify systemic issues and act collectively on behalf of Manchester practices.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="color:var(--colour-muted);line-height:1.75">The Manchester LMC uses breach reports to monitor the relationship between practices and the ICB, NHS Trusts, and other commissioning bodies. Where patterns emerge, we can escalate concerns collectively — protecting individual practices while addressing the underlying issue.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to report -->
  <section class="section section--neutral" aria-labelledby="what-to-report-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:780px;margin:0 auto">
        <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-6)">
          <span class="section-eyebrow">Guidance</span>
          <h2 id="what-to-report-heading">What Should You Report?</h2>
          <p>The following categories cover the most common types of contractual breach. If your situation does not fit neatly into one of these, please use the "Other" option in the form below.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion">

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-btn" aria-expanded="false">
              Referral Thresholds
              <svg class="accordion-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel">
              <p>Report this when an ICB or commissioner imposes inappropriate referral limits that prevent you from referring patients in line with your clinical judgement. This includes blanket restrictions, prior-authorisation requirements not agreed in your contract, and targets that compromise patient safety.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Numerical caps on referrals to specific specialties</li>
                <li>Requirements to obtain commissioner approval before referring</li>
                <li>Financial penalties or informal pressure linked to referral rates</li>
                <li>Mandated use of alternative pathways that do not meet patient needs</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-btn" aria-expanded="false">
              Pathway Breaches
              <svg class="accordion-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel">
              <p>Report this when commissioners or NHS Trusts make changes to agreed care pathways without proper consultation with practices or the LMC. Practices are entitled to be consulted before pathway changes take effect.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Unilateral changes to discharge or follow-up protocols</li>
                <li>Removal of secondary care services redirected to primary care without resource</li>
                <li>New or amended pathways imposed without a consultation period</li>
                <li>Changes that create additional workload without corresponding funding</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-btn" aria-expanded="false">
              Data Sharing Requests
              <svg class="accordion-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel">
              <p>Report this when your practice receives demands to share patient data that are inappropriate, lack a lawful basis, or fall outside agreed data sharing arrangements.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Requests for bulk patient data without a clear lawful basis</li>
                <li>Pressure to provide data to commercial or third-party organisations</li>
                <li>Requirements to use systems that extract data without explicit practice agreement</li>
                <li>Requests that conflict with your Data Protection Officer's advice</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-btn" aria-expanded="false">
              Appointment &amp; Workload Impositions
              <svg class="accordion-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel">
              <p>Report this when the ICB or NHS England imposes unsafe workload requirements — including minimum appointment numbers, staffing ratios, or access targets — that create an unreasonable risk to patient safety or GP wellbeing.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Mandated minimum daily appointment numbers without resource support</li>
                <li>Access targets (e.g. same-day quotas) imposed without funding</li>
                <li>Requirements to accept patient lists beyond safe registered list capacity</li>
                <li>Directives to operate with staffing levels you consider clinically unsafe</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-btn" aria-expanded="false">
              Enhanced Service Non-payment
              <svg class="accordion-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel">
              <p>Report this when your practice has delivered agreed enhanced services but payment has been withheld, delayed without explanation, or disputed by the ICB on grounds not set out in the original service specification.</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Non-payment beyond standard payment timescales</li>
                <li>Clawback of previously paid enhanced service fees without due process</li>
                <li>Retrospective changes to service specifications used to deny payment</li>
                <li>Disputes over eligibility criteria not made clear at service sign-up</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Form -->
  <section class="section" id="form" aria-labelledby="form-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:780px;margin:0 auto">

        <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-8)">
          <span class="section-eyebrow">Confidential Reporting</span>
          <h2 id="form-heading">Submit a Breach Report</h2>
          <p>Complete all required fields. Your information will only be seen by LMC officers and is handled in accordance with our privacy policy.</p>
        </div>

        <form action="https://formspree.io/f/placeholder" method="POST" data-ajax enctype="multipart/form-data" novalidate aria-label="Breach report form">

          <fieldset style="border:none;padding:0;margin:0 0 var(--space-8)">
            <legend style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.125rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--colour-primary);margin-bottom:var(--space-5);padding-bottom:var(--space-3);border-bottom:2px solid var(--colour-neutral);width:100%;display:block">Your Details</legend>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:var(--space-5)">
              <div class="form-group">
                <label class="form-label" for="reporter-name">Reporter Name <span class="required" aria-hidden="true">*</span></label>
                <input class="form-input" type="text" id="reporter-name" name="reporter_name" autocomplete="name" required aria-required="true" placeholder="Dr Jane Smith">
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <label class="form-label" for="practice-name">Practice Name <span class="required" aria-hidden="true">*</span></label>
                <input class="form-input" type="text" id="practice-name" name="practice_name" required aria-required="true" placeholder="Ancoats Medical Centre">
              </div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:var(--space-5)">
              <div class="form-group">
                <label class="form-label" for="reporter-role">Role</label>
                <select class="form-select" id="reporter-role" name="reporter_role">
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Select your role</option>
                  <option value="gp-partner">GP Partner</option>
                  <option value="salaried-gp">Salaried GP</option>
                  <option value="locum-gp">Locum GP</option>
                  <option value="practice-manager">Practice Manager</option>
                  <option value="nurse-ahp">Nurse / AHP</option>
                  <option value="other">Other</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <label class="form-label" for="reporter-email">Email Address <span class="required" aria-hidden="true">*</span></label>
                <input class="form-input" type="email" id="reporter-email" name="reporter_email" autocomplete="email" required aria-required="true" placeholder="jane.smith@nhs.net">
                <p class="form-hint">Used for follow-up only. Not shared externally.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset style="border:none;padding:0;margin:0 0 var(--space-8)">
            <legend style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.125rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--colour-primary);margin-bottom:var(--space-5);padding-bottom:var(--space-3);border-bottom:2px solid var(--colour-neutral);width:100%;display:block">Breach Details</legend>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label" for="organisation">ICB / Trust / Organisation Involved <span class="required" aria-hidden="true">*</span></label>
              <input class="form-input" type="text" id="organisation" name="organisation" required aria-required="true" placeholder="e.g. Greater Manchester Integrated Care Board">
            </div>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:var(--space-5)">
              <div class="form-group">
                <label class="form-label" for="breach-type">Breach Type</label>
                <select class="form-select" id="breach-type" name="breach_type">
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Select breach type</option>
                  <option value="referral-threshold">Referral Threshold</option>
                  <option value="care-pathway">Care Pathway</option>
                  <option value="data-sharing">Data Sharing</option>
                  <option value="workload-staffing">Workload / Staffing</option>
                  <option value="non-payment">Non-payment</option>
                  <option value="other">Other</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <label class="form-label" for="breach-date">Date of Breach</label>
                <input class="form-input" type="date" id="breach-date" name="breach_date">
                <p class="form-hint">Approximate date is fine if exact date is unknown.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label" for="breach-description">Description of Breach <span class="required" aria-hidden="true">*</span></label>
              <textarea class="form-textarea" id="breach-description" name="breach_description" rows="8" required aria-required="true" aria-describedby="description-hint" placeholder="Please describe what happened, who was involved, and how it has affected your practice or patients." style="min-height:200px"></textarea>
              <p class="form-hint" id="description-hint">Provide as much detail as possible. The more context you give, the more effectively we can act on your behalf.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label class="form-label" for="supporting-evidence">Supporting Evidence <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--colour-muted)">(optional)</span></label>
              <div style="border:1.5px dashed var(--colour-border);border-radius:var(--radius-md);padding:var(--space-6);text-align:center;background:var(--colour-neutral)">
                <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--colour-secondary)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" style="margin:0 auto var(--space-3)"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="17 8 12 3 7 8"/><line x1="12" y1="3" x2="12" y2="15"/></svg>
                <p style="margin:0 0 var(--space-3);color:var(--colour-muted);font-size:.9375rem">Click to browse or drag files here</p>
                <input type="file" id="supporting-evidence" name="supporting_evidence" accept=".pdf,.doc,.docx,.jpg,.png" multiple aria-describedby="file-hint">
                <p class="form-hint" id="file-hint" style="margin-top:var(--space-3)">Accepted: PDF, Word, JPEG, PNG. Max 10 MB per file.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset style="border:none;padding:0;margin:0 0 var(--space-8)">
            <legend style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.125rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--colour-primary);margin-bottom:var(--space-5);padding-bottom:var(--space-3);border-bottom:2px solid var(--colour-neutral);width:100%;display:block">Consent</legend>
            <div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-3);align-items:flex-start;padding:var(--space-5);background:var(--colour-neutral);border-radius:var(--radius-md);border:1.5px solid var(--colour-border)">
              <input type="checkbox" id="consent" name="consent" required aria-required="true" style="width:18px;height:18px;margin-top:2px;accent-color:var(--colour-secondary);flex-shrink:0;cursor:pointer">
              <label for="consent" style="font-size:.9375rem;line-height:1.65;cursor:pointer">I consent to Manchester LMC using this information to investigate and, where appropriate, raise this matter collectively on behalf of Manchester practices. I understand that my individual identity will not be disclosed without my explicit permission.</label>
            </div>
          </fieldset>

          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--space-5);flex-wrap:wrap">
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="22" y1="2" x2="11" y2="13"/><polygon points="22 2 15 22 11 13 2 9 22 2"/></svg>
              Submit Breach Report
            </button>
            <p style="font-size:.8125rem;color:var(--colour-muted);margin:0">Treated in strict confidence by LMC officers</p>
          </div>

        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What happens next -->
  <section class="section section--neutral" id="what-happens-next" aria-labelledby="next-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:780px;margin:0 auto">
        <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-8)">
          <span class="section-eyebrow">Process</span>
          <h2 id="next-heading">What Happens Next?</h2>
        </div>

        <ol style="list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--space-5)">
          <li style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-5);align-items:flex-start">
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:44px;height:44px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--colour-primary);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;flex-shrink:0">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="font-size:1rem;margin:0 0 var(--space-2)">Acknowledgement</h3>
              <p style="color:var(--colour-muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65">You will receive an automated acknowledgement email within 24 hours. An LMC officer will review your report within three working days.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-5);align-items:flex-start">
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:44px;height:44px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--colour-primary);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;flex-shrink:0">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="font-size:1rem;margin:0 0 var(--space-2)">Initial Assessment</h3>
              <p style="color:var(--colour-muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65">An LMC officer will assess whether the issue is isolated or part of a wider pattern. They may contact you for clarification using the email address provided.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-5);align-items:flex-start">
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:44px;height:44px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--colour-primary);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;flex-shrink:0">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="font-size:1rem;margin:0 0 var(--space-2)">Collective Action</h3>
              <p style="color:var(--colour-muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65">Where a systemic issue is identified, the LMC raises it collectively with the relevant commissioner or NHS body. Individual reports are anonymised unless you have agreed otherwise.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-5);align-items:flex-start">
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:44px;height:44px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--colour-primary);color:white;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;flex-shrink:0">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="font-size:1rem;margin:0 0 var(--space-2)">Feedback &amp; Outcome</h3>
              <p style="color:var(--colour-muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65">We will update you on the outcome. Where the issue cannot be resolved collectively, we can advise on individual options including formal grievance and contractual dispute processes.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div style="margin-top:var(--space-8);padding:var(--space-6);background:white;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);border:1px solid var(--colour-border);display:flex;gap:var(--space-5);align-items:flex-start">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--colour-accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:2px"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.6 1.18H6.6a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72 19.4 19.4 0 0 0 .7 2.81 2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.51 8.69a16 16 0 0 0 6 6l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45 19.4 19.4 0 0 0 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 22 15.92z"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size:1rem;margin:0 0 var(--space-2)">Need to speak to someone urgently?</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--colour-muted);margin:0 0 var(--space-3);line-height:1.65">If your situation requires immediate advice rather than a written report, please call us directly. Our officers are available Monday to Friday, 09:00–17:00.</p>
            <a href="tel:01612230032" class="link-arrow">0161 223 0032
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
